There are two solutions.

**First solution: Setting `height` to parent containers**

    html, body, .content {
      height:100%;
    }

**Second solution: Using viewport size**

    #chat-text {
      overflow: scroll;
      height: 50vh;
    }

In this solution, the `div` will take 50% of the viewport height. More on this can be found at [CSSTricks][1].


  [1]: https://css-tricks.com/viewport-sized-typography/

**Edit 1:** Using your code, it works for me. When adding the login-box `div`, that is when you get the issue because it takes 100% of the width and height and is on top of the chat box. For `#login-box.hidden`, change from:

    #login-box.hidden {
      display: hidden;
      opacity: 0;
    }

to:

    #login-box.hidden {
      display: none;
    }

`display: hidden;` is not a valid CSS rule.

