`CreatedAtRouteResult` or `CreatedAtRoute` are usually seen with Web API endpoints where the HTTP response code is required by the client.

With views one tends to see the Post/Redirect/Get approach

The `CreateAtRoute`  is a helper method which inherits from `ControllerBase` .  What `CreateAtRoute()` does  is  simply returning a new `CreatedAtRouteResult(routeName, routeValues, value) ` . There is no dark magic at all ([source code][1])

     /// &lt;summary&gt;
        /// Creates a &lt;see cref=&quot;CreatedAtRouteResult&quot;/&gt; object that produces a &lt;see cref=&quot;StatusCodes.Status201Created&quot;/&gt; response.
        /// &lt;/summary&gt;
        /// &lt;param name=&quot;routeName&quot;&gt;The name of the route to use for generating the URL.&lt;/param&gt;
        /// &lt;param name=&quot;value&quot;&gt;The content value to format in the entity body.&lt;/param&gt;
        /// &lt;returns&gt;The created &lt;see cref=&quot;CreatedAtRouteResult&quot;/&gt; for the response.&lt;/returns&gt;
        [NonAction]
        public virtual CreatedAtRouteResult CreatedAtRoute(string routeName, [ActionResultObjectValue] object value)
            =&gt; CreatedAtRoute(routeName, routeValues: null, value: value);

The `CreateAtRoute` method is often used within an `ApiController` , and the third parameter will be used as the content of response  . Let&#39;s say an action method :

    public class HomeController : Controller{

        public IActionResult Index(){
            return CreatedAtRoute(&quot;HelloDetails&quot;,new {Id=1} , new Student{
                Id = 1,
                StudentEmail = &quot;test@microsoft.com&quot;
            });
        }
    }
Then it will return the values with 201 status code without redirecting.

    {
        &quot;id&quot;: 1,
        &quot;studentEmail&quot;: &quot;test@microsoft.com&quot;
    }
While using `RedirectToAction`, it will redirect to another action and return the result of that action.

  [1]: https://github.com/aspnet/AspNetCore/blob/64157c95c1f10992e81e8590e31e90b0b8bd5eeb/src/Mvc/Mvc.Core/src/ControllerBase.cs#L2023

